syntax :

grep [pattern] [filename]

---------------------------------
global regular expreesion print

process and print matching patern 

use top serach specific paterns
-------------------------------
grep "OPTIONS" gg.txt   :will print matching statement .its case sensitive
grep -i "options" gg.txt  :will show all options present,i is for non case sensitive
grep -i "options" gg.txt t1.txt file.txt :multiple file can be use to serach
grep -i "options" * :wild card search,will search all files in directory
grep -v "options" gg.txt    :invert match.does not contain pattern lines will show.
grep --help: for help